The paper deals with pilot contamination in multi-cell multiuser massive MIMO networks, which is a problem in wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also discusses power allocation and capacity analysis, which are related to network optimization and performance evaluation, respectively. Hence, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely categories. The paper specifically focuses on massive MIMO networks, which is a subfield of wireless communication systems, and hence, cs.MM (Mobile Computing and Communication) is another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the design of pilot sequences, which is related to signal processing and communication theory, and hence, cs.COM (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category.
